===Verb===
{{en-verb|bottl|ing}}

# {{transitive}} To seal (a liquid) into a bottle for later consumption.
#: ''This plant '''bottles''' vast quantities of spring water every day.''
# {{context|transitive|British}} To feed (an infant) [[baby formula]].
#: ''Because of complications she can't breast feed her baby and so she '''bottles''' him.''
# {{context|British|slang}} To refrain from doing (something) at the last moment because of a sudden loss of courage.
#: ''The rider '''bottled''' the big jump.''
# {{context|British|slang}} To strike (someone) with a bottle.

